# Auto-push to GitHub

Remote repository: https://github.com/ybnr512-11/20260622.git

After completing any code or content change in this project:

1. Run `git status`, `git diff`, and `git log -1` to review changes.
2. Stage only project files (do not commit secrets).
3. Commit with a concise message describing why the change was made.
4. Push to `origin` on the current branch (`git push origin HEAD`).

If the repo is not initialized, run `git init`, add the remote, create the first commit, and push with `-u origin main`.

Only skip push when the user explicitly says not to push, or when push fails due to auth/network (report the error and what the user should fix).
